summary: The document is a memo from November 9, 1995, focusing on the tracking and identification of microfilm reels associated with the JFK assassination records. It outlines the initial confusion and subsequent resolution regarding the storage and labeling of these records, specifically mentioning boxes 80T01614R and 80T01357A. The memo concludes by stating that the microfilm reels from box 80T01614R have been integrated into box 64 of job number 80T01357A, with plans to update the records accordingly.
key_findings: The memo clarifies the confusion surrounding the contents and labeling of boxes related to the JFK assassination records.
It indicates that microfilm reels from box 80T01614R were likely moved to box 64 of job number 80T01357A.
The document sheds light on the complexities and challenges of maintaining accurate historical records.
It notes the participation of several individuals and departments, including OCA, the History Staff, and Russ Holmes, in the oversight of these records.
